  "text": "T is a vector valued harmonic Maass form of weight 1/2 for the dual Weil representationρ. We see that its principal part is given by q −1/24 (e 1 − e 5 + e 7 − e 11 ). The function (η(z)η(2z)η(3z)η(6z)) 2 in the denominator of F is a cusp form of weight 4 for Γ 0 (6) which is invariant under all Atkin-Lehner involutions W 6 d for d | 6, and the numerator of F equals E 4 |(W 6 1 + W 6 2 − W 6 3 − W 6 6 ). Thus F is an eigenfunction of all AtkinLehner involutions, with eigenvalue 1 for W 6 1 and W 6 2 , and eigenvalue −1 for W 6 3 and W 6 6 . In particular, the Fourier expansions of F at the cusps of Γ 0 (6) are essentially the same, up to a possible minus sign. Using the formula for the Fourier expansion of the Millson lift given in Theorem 5.1 of [CITATION_1] , it is now straightforward to check that F lifts to a harmonic Maass form I M (F, τ ) of weight 1/2 forρ, having twice the principal part asH (recall that we multiplied the Millson lift by i/ √ N ). In view of Lemma 2.3, this implies that the differencẽ H − (F, τ ) . The holomorphic coefficients of I M (F, τ ) at q (24n−r 2 )/24 e r for r 2 − 24n < 0 are given by",
